definitions: a person who makes a lower bid than someone else in an auction or when seeking a contract

examples.text: the sale yielded a number of disappointed underbidders

shortDefinitions: person who makes lower bid than someone in auction or competitive tendering

definitions: a person who makes a lower bid on their hand than its strength warrants

examples.text: would you rather face an overbidder or an underbidder?

shortDefinitions: person who makes lower bid on their hand than its strength warrants
